# Red-team engine bundle source (M2-B3).
#
# PyRIT is the MVP AI/LLM red-team engine (Microsoft, MIT — github.com/microsoft/PyRIT).
# It is a heavy dependency (107 resolved packages incl. transformers/scipy/pandas/lxml),
# so it is deliberately kept OUT of the base uv.lock and installed only into the
# dedicated `redteam` worker image stage. Rationale: the block-on-High SCA gate runs
# osv-scanner against uv.lock — keeping PyRIT out of uv.lock isolates its large
# transitive-dependency blast radius from the base image and the base SCA/Trivy gates.
#
# Pinned exact (CLAUDE.md §3 / SECURITY_DEVELOPMENT_PLAN §7 supply-chain pinning).
# Regenerate the hash-locked bundle after any bump (--universal so platform-gated
# transitives like greenlet are pinned for the linux image, not just the dev host):
#   uv pip compile --generate-hashes --universal --python-version 3.12 \
#     requirements-redteam.in -o requirements-redteam.txt
pyrit==0.14.0
